Elastic Load Balancer (ELB)

What is an Elastic Load Balancer?

An Elastic Load Balancer (ELB) is an AWS service that distributes incoming traffic across multiple EC2 instances.

This helps improve availability, performance, and reliability.

Real-Life Example

Imagine a supermarket with 4 billing counters.

If all customers stand at one counter, it becomes slow.

Instead, a staff member directs customers to different counters.

👉 That staff member is like an Elastic Load Balancer.

Why Do We Use ELB?
Distributes traffic across multiple servers.
Prevents a single server from becoming overloaded.
Improves application availability.
Automatically sends traffic only to healthy EC2 instances.
