Types of Load Balancers
Application Load Balancer (ALB) → For HTTP/HTTPS web applications (Layer 7).
Network Load Balancer (NLB) → For high-performance TCP/UDP traffic (Layer 4).
Gateway Load Balancer (GWLB) → Used with virtual network appliances like firewalls.
