Easy Way to Remember

ELB = Traffic Manager

Just like a traffic police officer directs vehicles to different roads to avoid traffic jams, an Elastic Load Balancer directs user requests to different EC2 instances so that no single server becomes overloaded.



the 3 types of Elastic Load Balancers in a very simple and easy-to-remember way.

1. Application Load Balancer (ALB)
What is it?

ALB distributes HTTP and HTTPS web traffic to multiple EC2 instances.

Used For
Websites
Web Applications
APIs
Example

Suppose you open:

www.amazon.com

The ALB receives your request and sends it to one of the available web servers.

Easy to Remember:

ALB = Web Traffic (HTTP/HTTPS)

2. Network Load Balancer (NLB)
What is it?

NLB distributes TCP, UDP, and TLS traffic.

It is designed for very high speed and low latency applications.

Used For
Gaming applications
Banking applications
Video streaming
Real-time applications
Example

A bank processes thousands of transactions every second.

NLB handles this traffic quickly with very low delay.

Easy to Remember:

NLB = Fast Network Traffic

3. Gateway Load Balancer (GWLB)
What is it?

GWLB distributes traffic to security appliances such as firewalls and intrusion detection systems.

Used For
Firewalls
Security inspection
Network monitoring
Example

Before traffic reaches your EC2 instance, it passes through a firewall to check for malicious requests.

GWLB sends traffic to the firewall first.

Easy to Remember:

GWLB = Security Traffic

